description: A React functional component named TopNav that renders a right-aligned navigation bar with a list of links, which are customizable via props. It uses semantic HTML elements and accessibility attributes.

methods.name: TopNav({ items = ['Home', 'Blog', 'Services', 'Location'] })
methods.description: A React functional component that displays a navigation menu with links provided via props, defaulting to ['Home', 'Blog', 'Services', 'Location']. It renders a header containing a nav element with a list of clickable links.
